sac.examples.helloworldgraph

Class HelloWorldGraphState

  • java.lang.Object
    • sac.StateImpl
      • sac.graph.GraphStateImpl
        • sac.examples.helloworldgraph.HelloWorldGraphState
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<State>, GraphState, Graphvizable, State

    public class HelloWorldGraphState
extends GraphStateImpl
    'Hello World' example for a graph. Given a directed graph (assigned via a static field), it shows how: children nodes can be generated, identifiers can be produced, and cost functions (g, h) can be attached to a search state.
    Author:
    Przemysław Klęsk (wi.zut.edu.pl), Marcin Korzeń (wi.zut.edu.pl)
